HEADWORD: Darbyite
<hw>Dar"by*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the Plymouth
Brethren, or of a sect among them; -- so called from John N.
<xex>Darby</xex>, one of the leaders of the Brethren.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

